Description: 1999 Plum purple Parker Fly. Love this guitar and did a lot of gigs with it. Very stable trustworthy guitar that never let me down. I have too many guitars and have taken to strats so I need to thin the herd. Has a few scratches. I am the only owner. Bought it from Guitar center in 2000 I think. It had been dropped and there was a small crack where the strap peg is. I had it professionally repaired and then did a little touch up on the paint myself so it looks like a scar near the float adjuster. There was never a problem with it. Everything works great. The LED light for the battery is missing but I never used it anyway. Battery lasts a long time. I would replace every 6 months regardless if it needed it because it was a gig guitar. Comes with a Parker hard shell case. I just played this guitar for 30 min before reposting. Everything works like a dream. All pick up selections work and Piezo is great. Action is set really low. Every fret is the same across the neck.
Title: Parker Fly Deluxe Guitar USA 1999 With HSC plum/purple
ConditionDescription: Very good condition Parker Fly.  Stainless steel frets are in perfect condition.  Has some cosmetic dings but is in almost perfect working condition.   The red battery LED is missing.  Battery would usually last me 400 plus hours.   Had a crack that was long ago repaired and is structurally sound.  Whammy bar and HSC included.  The string tension bar is for 10s.   I also have the 9 plate for the vibrato and the allen wrenches.
